Subject: National Council of Unions of the Industrial and Lower Income Group of Government Workers 
To: Christina
Content:
The National Council of Unions of the Industrial and Lower Income Group of Government Workers (MKTR) is a national trade union center in Malaysia. The MKTR is a National Labour Centre consisting of twenty-two (22) affiliated national and state unions representing over 200,000 workers in the Lower-income Group, commonly known as category ``C and ``D or Sub-ordinate (Supportive) Groups from the Public Sector. The MKTR has 45,000 dues paying members.[1] The MKTR is affiliated with the International Trade Union Confederation. 
